<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id14b0b996-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d" identifier="/us/usc/t21/s875"><num value="875">§ 875.</num><heading> Administrative hearings</heading><subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="id14b0b997-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d" identifier="/us/usc/t21/s875/a"><num value="a" class="bold">(a)</num><heading class="bold"> Power of Attorney General</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">In carrying out his functions under this subchapter, the Attorney General may hold hearings, sign and issue subpenas, administer oaths, examine witnesses, and receive evidence at any place in the United States.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="id14b0b998-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d" identifier="/us/usc/t21/s875/b"><num value="b" class="bold">(b)</num><heading class="bold"> Procedures applicable</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Except as otherwise provided in this subchapter, notice shall be given and hearings shall be conducted under appropriate procedures of subchapter II of chapter 5 of title 5.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<sourceCredit id="id14b0b999-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d">(<ref href="/us/pl/91/513/tII/s505">Pub. L. 91–513, title II, § 505</ref>, <date date="1970-10-27">Oct. 27, 1970</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/84/1272">84 Stat. 1272</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
